<br>
Epic had BO 4 and damage shield up and mask<br>
The epic did its usual outstanding job. It killed the first mob much quicker than air did. Ended fight at 30% health, extremely slow regeneration<br>
<br>
Ward of Xegony had BO4 and cadeau of flame and mask<br>
I ran this test twice<br>
First time was better. Pet rampaged at 20% health. I had to cast heal about 3 times to keep it alive at the end. As before, I only nuked each target once with SoFB.<br>
<br>
Second fight was abyssmal. The air pet didn't rampage, and I had to chain cast heal with SoFB on the targets so that I didnt have to run. Ended fight with pet at 20 and me at 20m.<br>
<br>
The 61 air pet DOES have exceptional regeneration. It should be noted that it could regen 80% of its health by the time I meditated 30m back (I have FT1 only). Air pet definitely doesnt seem like a better tank than the epic at this point, and it's overall DPS can't compare to the epic. I believe this -may- change if it was equipped with proccing weapons, but as you can also equip the epic with the same weapons and also gain extra attacks, I don't see that as anything worthwhile to compare.<br>
<br>
In closing, the 61 air pet is a decent pet, and people without epics are gonna frigging love it just for the regen alone(and the fact that its lvl 60). <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27498">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27498</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
