Canvashan <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=canvashan>canvashan</A> at: 10/26/02 6:44:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shadextinkerdink>Shadex Tinkerdink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 524<br> <font color=#333333>(10/26/02 6:56:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7583.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Additional notes</span><hr size=1> Well, keep in mind the epic has more hp than the air pet.  Its possible that the air pet regens faster, but i bet a large portion is simply an illusion from the hp.<br>
<br>
If you have epic and air pet, i see it like this.  Use epic pet for exp and use air pet on bosses.  The air pet has been stated to melee similarly to the epic minus the proc.  Add procing weapons to the air pet and it will outdamage epic pet on mobs where the epic procs wont land.<br>
<br>
Epic = exp, or if your undecided on what pet to use<br>
Air (possibly all new pets?) = bosses and special situations <p>&lt;A HREF=&quot;http://shade.austin2600.org&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://shade.austin2600.org/fishsig1.jpg&quot;&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;<br>
