<br>
<br>
Just wait for 65 earth <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Ylaine D'esibour<br>
62 Arch Mage</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dilandumatador>Dilandu Matador</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#333333>(10/26/02 8:14:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7583.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   well...</span><hr size=1> It really depends on what level mobs your fighting...<br>
<br>
In the history of exp'ing i've found that if a pet is higher level than said mob, it just tears it apart.<br>
<br>
What i've found... Epic just rips apart mobs that are below level 50.  If its 55+ or basically anything in PoP, the air pet ends up ahead, albeit by a small margin.  <br>
<br>
Been testing this alot trying to figure it all out... But the level does play a factor in fighting higher level mobs, for sure.<br>
<br>
<br>
As a side note, did a duel today with a focus'd epic and a focus'd 61 air pet.  No dmg shield on either, but burnout 4 + muzzle on both.  Air pet won with about 20% health remaining.  <br>
<br>
